ca.uqac.lif.labpal

Class Namer

  • java.lang.Object
    • ca.uqac.lif.labpal.Namer
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    LatexNamer, TitleNamer

    public abstract class Namer
extends java.lang.Object
    Object that automatically builds a description for a table or plot object, based on the parameters that have been used to create it.

    2.11
    Author:

      • latexify

        public static java.lang.String latexify(java.lang.String s)
        Replaces illegal characters in a LaTeX string by legal ones. Since identifiers in LaTeX commands can only have letters, numbers and other symbols must be replaced into something else to create a valid identifier. The basic replacement scheme is to change every occurrence of a digit into a unique letter that somehow "looks" like the digit.
        Parameters:
        s - The string to replace
        Returns:
        The replaced string
